$ Shell command: tzselect
@ tzselect

`tzselect` asks a few questions about someone's location and will then print this user's → Linux/timezone[timezone],
such as `Europe/Zurich`.

sa:

  → development/date-time/time-zone

  → Linux/shell/commands/index[Shell commands]

  The Windows command line utility → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/tzutil_exe[`tzutil.exe`]
